Main Branch 1.0.83499 Release 2026-05-06

Headline Changes

Crossbow strength buff
Tech cost rebalancing
New Map Search function 

Design

Crossbows now have +50% strength against melee, instead of +50% attack
Tech costs for columns in the tech tree changed to 100, 150, 250, 400, 700, 1100, 1600 (from 80, 120, 200, 400, 600, 1000, 1600)
Increased flat science from difficulty level by 2
At least two non-trashable tech cards will be offered if possible, to prevent all tech choices being bonus cards
Slingers are now obsolete at Bodkin arrow (previously also required Windlass)
Gold and Silver mine output increased to 50 money (from 40)
Reduced culture requirements for Market class improvements (Market requires Weak, Grocer Developing and Fair Strong) and adjusted some ambitions accordingly
Units can repair any improvement they can build (affects Disciples and Brahmins)
Ship build queue options added for each harbor in a city, in addition to each body of water that does not have a harbor, to allow choosing where the ship spawns
Improved city site distribution for 2-team maps
AIs will no longer have child leaders, instead using the next adult in the succession or generating a new character if needed
Rising Star trait now replaces Infamous and Unpopular
All Hindu cities can now build Brahmins, without requiring Holy City/State Religion/Tolerance (Empires of the Indus)
Decreased Indian Unique Unit vision to be in line with other units, with the exception of Steppe Riders which retain extra vision (Empires of the Indus)
The owner of the unit, not the upgrading player, needs Polis to upgrade Steppe Riders (Empires of the Indus)
Mahapadma's unknown mother now has a name (Empires of the Indus)
Added Phidias, a Builder Artist, as a starting courtier to the Pericles dynasty (Heroes of the Aegean / Wonders and Dynasties)
Can no longer recruit Fanatic Raid units in the Wrath of Gods scenario (Wrath of Gods)
Slightly reduced frequency of Jade spawning (Empires of the Indus)

Programming

Renderer initialization split across four 4 frames instead of 1
Improved performance when rendering timeline GIFs
Moved the minimum number of non-trashable techs offered to XML (MIN_NON_TRASHABLE_TECHS_AVAILABLE)
Stale network games are cleared from the database on failed connection
Potential improvements to Bluetooth audio output
Replaced custom map element names with TextTypes on Empires of the Indus premade maps
Family Control scores are now moddable (Empires of the Indus)

UI

Added Map Search function, accessed via the magnifying glass icon on the top left of minimap.  Can search for Cities, Units, Improvements and Resources, by player
Added Tech Tree to Extras menu, to allow viewing the tree without being in a game
Added banded overlay effect for cities that will soon have a religion due to building a shrine when the religion is selected
When selecting a unit with a General, the General name is now shown in brackets instead of replacing the unit name
Added a Mission concept to help explain the Maurya ability
Score list now sorts Wonders and Holy Site VPs together
Map element names now take priority over family-defined first city names
Unit effect tooltips show to the right of the promotions panel
Pressing ALT now shows health bar damage preview of non-hostile units, in addition to the damage preview text that is displayed without ALT
Specialists on pillaged tiles are now shown in most city UI counts, with warning color
Map cameras now adjust the center of their view to avoid featuring large out-of-bounds areas
Handling of possessive character names now language dependent
Updated Map Size tooltip to show the actual maximum player count
Bridges now only render over rivers when a road segment is present on the tile leading up to it
AddImprovement bonus is no longer valid when the only valid tiles already have improvements
Added warning text and hint to use CTRL when placing a bonus improvement on a tile with an existing improvement
Religion overlay is now displayed, at a lower opacity, for cities that will soon have a religion (eg via Shrine construction)
Added Ruthless AI text explanation to AI opinion due to being close to winning or having an alliance
Reworked event helptext for "subject not" - "Not Character is X" is now "Character is not X"
Added more detailed mission menu button info
Premade map selection with restricted nations is no longer saved, to prevent issues with leaders not appearing on Choose Leader screen
Localized text updates
No Organized Tribes option renamed to mention the Huns (Empires of the Indus)
Tamil leaders show their preset family on the dynasty selection tooltip (Empires of the Indus)
Updated portrait selections for some Hun portrait sequences to reduce artifacting (Empires of the Indus)

